Class EdgeMatchFilter

All Implemented Interfaces:
Filter<LFEdge>
public class EdgeMatchFilter
extends CompositeFilter<LFEdge>

A filter for LF edges based on a set of match type criteria. Instances of this class compare a specified basis edge based on their match type criteria. This class extends CompositeFilter, and the constructors add various filters as members depending on the criteria in effect.

Edge match filters use the following match types as criteria in addition to the ones used by VertexMatchFilter: MatchType.LABEL_MATCH, and MatchType.LABEL_MISMATCH.

Author:
Scott Martin
See Also:
VertexMatchFilter, LabelMatchFilter

EdgeMatchFilter

public EdgeMatchFilter(LFEdge basis,
                       Collection<MatchType> matchTypes)
Creates a new edge match filter based on the specified edge, using the specified match type criteria. Depending on the criteria, this constructor adds instances of VertexMatchFilter and LabelMatchFilter (or their inverses) to the set of filters composing it.

Parameters:
basis - The LF edge to use for comparison.
matchTypes - The comparison criteria, used to populate this composite filter.
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if basis is null.
